Troubleshooting: Identify and resolve issues related to MEP systems during construction or operation. 
MEP engineers should possess problem-solving skills to address unexpected challenges that may arise during the project lifecycle.

Innovation and Research: Stay informed about the latest advancements in MEP technologies. 
Propose innovative solutions to enhance system performance, energy efficiency, and sustainability.

Team Collaboration: Work effectively within a multidisciplinary team, collaborating with architects, 
structural engineers, contractors, and other professionals involved in the project. 
Effective teamwork is crucial for the successful implementation of MEP systems.
